[[File:Serrita.gif|thumb|right|180px|Serrita Municipality Flag]] '''Serrita''' is a city in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. The population in 2009, according with [[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|IBGE]] was 18.958 inhabitants and the total area is 1603.6&nbsp;km².
==Geography==
* State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Sertão]] Pernambucano * Boundaries - Ceará state ('''N'''); [[Parnamirim, Pernambuco|Parnamirim]] and [[Terra Nova, Pernambuco|Terra Nova]] ('''S'''); [[Salgueiro]] and [[Cedro]] ('''E'''); [[Moreilândia]] and [[Granito]] ('''W'''). * Area - 1603.6&nbsp;km² * Elevation - 419 m * Hidrography - [[Brigida River|Brigida]] and [[Terra Nova River|Terra Nova rivers]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[hiperxerófila]] * Clima - [[semi arid]] - ([[Sertão]]) hot * Annual average temperature - 27.0 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 535.5&nbsp;km
==Economy==
The main economic activities in '''Serrita''' are based in [[agribusiness]], especially creation of [[goat]]s, [[sheep]], [[pigs]]s, [[cattle]], [[horses]], [[donkeys]], [[chickens]]; and plantations of [[onions]], [[beans]] and [[banana]]s.
